That markdown is already very clean; adding just a bit of styling will make it classroom‑ready while staying simple to convert.

Here’s a version with minimal CSS that Pandoc or most Markdown–to–PDF systems will respect:

```markdown
---
title: "Compassionate Containment: A Grounded Listening Guide"
page_number: true
css: "style.css"
---

> **Educational Note**  
> *This guide is for skills practice and teaching only.*  
> It does not replace professional mental‑health care.  
> In crises, reach out: US – **988** (call or text) | International – [https://findahelpline.com](https://findahelpline.com)

---

# Core Sequence
**Reflect → Validate → Ground → Explore → Refer / Boundary**

| Step | Purpose | Typical Language |
|------|----------|------------------|
| **Reflect** | Show understanding of emotion. | “It sounds like you’re …” |
| **Validate** | Normalize feelings; reduce shame. | “Anyone in your situation might feel that way.” |
| **Ground** | Calm the body before problem‑solving. | “Let’s take a slow breath together.” |
| **Explore** | Restore agency with gentle curiosity. | “What helps you feel even a bit steadier?” |
| **Refer / Boundary** | Maintain safety; encourage professional help. | “If this becomes too heavy, reach out to 988 or a local service.” |

---

# Practice Dialogues

## Everyday Anxiety
**Person:** “I’ve been so tense I can’t concentrate at work.”  
**Supporter:**  
- **Reflect:** “It sounds like your stress is making focus hard.”  
- **Validate:** “That’s understandable; anyone under that pressure might feel distracted.”  
- **Ground:** “Let’s take two slower breaths—notice how your shoulders drop slightly.”  
- **Explore:** “What helps you reset before tasks?”  
- **Refer / Boundary:** “If stress keeps interfering, consider talking with a counselor or doctor.”

## Acute Distress
**Person:** “I feel hopeless; I don’t know how to go on.”  
**Supporter:**  
- **Reflect:** “You’re feeling exhausted and unsure where to turn.”  
- **Validate:** “Those feelings make sense after what you’ve been facing.”  
- **Ground:** “Let’s steady the breath together—feel the floor supporting you.”  
- **Explore:** “What’s helped you feel even a tiny bit safer before?”  
- **Refer / Boundary:** “You deserve immediate support. If you ever feel unsafe, call or text **988** (U.S.) or use [findahelpline.com](https://findahelpline.com) for local help.”

---

> **Safety Reminder**  
> This material is non‑clinical and educational.  
> For emotional crisis, contact **988** (U.S.) or go to [findahelpline.com](https://findahelpline.com).

```

